---
layout: default
title: "F-13 — Brewery Activation Workflow"
permalink: /docs/brewery-activation/
description: "Mandatory DraftVerify workflow for activating NFC-tagged non-alcoholic kegs at the brewery prior to distribution."
---

<section class="section">
  <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">

<div class="kicker">DraftVerify Standards Library · F-13</div>
<h1>Brewery Activation Workflow</h1>

<p style="font-size:0.95rem;color:#6b7280;">
Version 1.0 · Publication Date: 2025-01-01 · Status: Active<br>
© 2025 DraftVerify™ Standards Initiative. All rights reserved.
</p>

<p>
This document defines the <strong>mandatory activation sequence</strong> for NFC-tagged non-alcoholic kegs prepared
under the DraftVerify Standard.  
Activation is the moment a serialized tag becomes <strong>live in the DraftVerify Registry</strong> and officially
linked to a specific product, batch, and keg.
</p>

<p>
No NA keg may enter distribution without full activation.  
Unactivated kegs are <strong>not DraftVerify compliant</strong>.
</p>

  </div>
</section>



<!-- SECTION 1 -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">

<h2>1.0 Purpose</h2>

<p>
The purpose of activation is to ensure every NA keg leaving the brewery has:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>A <strong>verified NFC identity</strong> created under F-12</li>
  <li>A <strong>confirmed product assignment</strong></li>
  <li>A <strong>traceable batch linkage</strong></li>
  <li>A <strong>permanent registry record</strong> beginning at the source</li>
  <li>A <strong>validated NA-only production path</strong></li>
</ul>

<p>
Activation creates the first immutable entry in the DraftVerify chain-of-custody.
</p>

  </div>
</section>



<!-- SECTION 2 -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">

<h2>2.0 Required Tools & Conditions</h2>

<p>Breweries must use:</p>

<ul>
  <li>DraftVerify Encoder App (mobile or desktop)</li>
  <li>DraftVerify Registry connection (API or portal)</li>
  <li>Serialized NFC tag (completed under F-12)</li>
  <li>Valid product record in the brewery’s DV product list</li>
  <li>Batch number or production code</li>
  <li>Staff authentication (username or encoded staff ID)</li>
</ul>

<p>
Activation must occur in an <strong>NA-only staging area</strong> or clean room prior to entering storage.
</p>

  </div>
</section>



<!-- SECTION 3 -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">

<h2>3.0 Activation Data Requirements</h2>

<p>
The following information must be captured during activation:
</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>NFC Identity:</strong> DV-KG-YYYY-BREWERYCODE-#####</li>
  <li><strong>Product Name / Style</strong> (must match DV product database)</li>
  <li><strong>Batch Number / Lot Code</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Fill Date</strong> (YYYY-MM-DD)</li>
  <li><strong>Keg Size</strong> (20L / 30L / 50L, etc.)</li>
  <li><strong>NA-Only Verification</strong> (confirm system used was NA-only)</li>
  <li><strong>Operator ID</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Timestamp</strong></li>
</ul>

<p>
All fields are mandatory. Missing fields invalidate the activation.
</p>

  </div>
</section>



<!-- SECTION 4 -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">

<h2>4.0 Activation Workflow (MUST FOLLOW ORDER)</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Scan serialized NFC tag</li>
  <li>Verify identity format (must pass F-12 rules)</li>
  <li>Select product from DV product list</li>
  <li>Enter batch or lot number</li>
  <li>Confirm NA-only production path</li>
  <li>Enter fill date & keg size</li>
  <li>Confirm operator ID (auto-pulled if possible)</li>
  <li>Submit activation to DraftVerify Registry</li>
  <li>Wait for confirmation: <strong>“ACTIVATED — VALID”</strong></li>
  <li>Move keg to <strong>NA-only cold room</strong></li>
</ol>

<p>
If confirmation is not received, the keg cannot be shipped.
</p>

  </div>
</section>



<!-- SECTION 5 -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">

<h2>5.0 Rejection & Exception Handling</h2>

<p>A keg activation must be rejected if:</p>

<ul>
  <li>NFC tag identity does not pass validation</li>
  <li>Tag shows as previously activated</li>
  <li>Incorrect brewery code appears</li>
  <li>Product does not match brewery’s DV list</li>
  <li>UID conflict is detected</li>
  <li>Metadata mismatch occurs (year, serial, etc.)</li>
</ul>

<p>
Rejected activations must be logged and flagged with a <strong>“DO NOT SHIP”</strong> status
until corrected through the DraftVerify Portal.
</p>

  </div>
</section>



<!-- SECTION 6 -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">

<h2>6.0 Chain-of-Custody Record</h2>

<p>
Upon successful activation, the Registry generates a permanent, immutable record containing:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>NFC identity & UID</li>
  <li>Product assignment</li>
  <li>Batch/lot number</li>
  <li>Operator ID</li>
  <li>Timestamp</li>
  <li>Location (Brewery → NA Cold Room)</li>
</ul>

<p>
This becomes the <strong>origin point</strong> for all downstream distributor and venue verification.
</p>

  </div>
</section>



<!-- SECTION 7 -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">

<h2>7.0 Compliance Requirements</h2>

<ul>
  <li>All NA kegs must be activated <strong>before</strong> entering storage or shipping.</li>
  <li>Activation must occur in an NA-only area.</li>
  <li>Operators must be individually authenticated.</li>
  <li>Daily activation logs must be reviewed by a supervisor.</li>
</ul>

<p>
Failure to activate invalidates DraftVerify compliance for the entire keg.
</p>

  </div>
</section>



